A CAN Frame holds vehicle info as follows
ID : 0x100, 1st & 2nd byte holds speed, 3rd & 4th byte holds rpm, 5th byte holds fuel level, 6th byte holds driving mode
ID : 0x101, 1st & 2nd byte holds speed
ID : 0x102, 1st & 2nd bytes holds rpm
ID : 0x103, 1st byte holds fuel level
ID : 0x104, 1st byte holds driving mode

Modify the MCP server which returns a JSON payload as per incoming CAN Frame
